David's dwm build
=================

My own, somewhat opinionated, build of the dwm window manager, patched
to suit my own needs.

Dependencies
============

Aside from the usual dependencies for dwm, this build needs the following
software in order to run as it is configured. Pretty much all of this can
be changed in the config.def.h.

 -	Terminal emulator - ghostty
 -	Web browser - firefox
 -	Launcher menu - rofi
 -	Notification daemon - dunst
 -	Wallpaper setting - nitrogen
 -	Compositor - picom

 Patches
 =======

 The following patches have been applied, in order:

 -	alpha (transparency in the title bar)
 -	xrdb (define colorscheme in .Xresources)
 	- requires modification of the xrdb() function to include alphas
 -	cfacts-vanitygaps (adds gaps between client windows, and also
 	horixontal resizing)
 -	removebordersonmonocle (does what it says on the tin)
 -	restartsig (restart without leaving dwm)
 -	preserveonrestart (saves window positions when restarting)
 -	cool-autostart (autostart, defined within config.h)
 -	attachaside (spawn new windows on the right and top)
 -	pertag-togglelayout (differing layouts on tags, and toggling of
 	layouts)
 -	rotatestack (move selected window through the stack)
 -	floatpos (define keybindings and rules to position floating windows)
 -	actualfullscreen (toggle fullscreen with a key binding)
 -	adjacentags (move back and forth through tags using keybinds)
 -	status2d (adds tags for colourful status bar)
 -	status2d-xrdb (add definitation for terminal colors to status2d)

